# Project Governance Rules

- Check changes against `docs/SPEC.md`, `docs/ARCH.md`, and `docs/RULES.md`.
- Read the relevant `docs/TASKS/*.md` before implementation.
- Flag any change crossing module boundaries without updating `docs/ARCH.md`.
- Flag changes to API, schema, event, file format, or CLI without a matching `docs/CONTRACTS/` update.
- Flag handlers that bypass `api/feedback` and access `api/persistence` directly from `web/dashboard` or `cli/`.
- Flag `integrations/*` code that imports from `api/feedback` or `api/persistence`.
- Flag any log statement that includes a raw email field.
- Flag any new `any` type in production code.
- Prefer small local rewrites during review; do not perform broad rewrites unless the task asks.
- Escalate risky changes (auth, schema, destructive ops, deployment) to the human before merge.
